<section id="reflection" class="reflection">

<span class="section-tag">
FINAL REFLECTION
</span>

<h2>
What I Learned
</h2>

<div class="reflection-card">

<h3>
Engineering is Organized Chaos
</h3>

<p>

Engineering Problems brought together everything I had learned over the past three years. CAD, teamwork, communication, testing, redesign, and problem-solving all happened under real deadlines. It was the closest experience I had to working on an actual engineering team.

</p>

<div class="reflection-grid">

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Biggest Lesson</h4>

<p>

USE THE SCRUM BOARD.

Organization keeps projects moving.

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Favorite Challenge</h4>

<p>

🥚 Trebuchet Egg Toss (3rd Place)

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Hardest Challenge</h4>

<p>

Battle of the Bridges (4th Place)

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Advice for Future Students</h4>

<p>

LEARN HOW TO ROW.

Seriously.

</p>

</div>

</div>

<div class="reflection-card" style="margin-top:40px;">

<h3>
Funniest Memory
</h3>

<p>

The entire Cardboard Boat Regatta.

Weeks of engineering... only to discover that building the boat was only half the challenge.

Actually rowing it was the other half.

Needless to say... we found that out the hard way.

</p>

</div>

